======================================================================
THM-155 FROM SIGN ALTERNATION at p=11
======================================================================
  c5 + 2*ov2 = 924

  Implication: h_hat_ov2 = -h_hat_c5 / 2
  So ov2 Walsh has OPPOSITE sign to c5 Walsh at every pair.
    (1,3): h_hat_c5 =    -5.5000 (sign -), h_hat_ov2 =     2.7500 (sign +), chi(ab) = +
          c5 sign matches -chi(ab)? YES, ov2 sign matches chi(ab)? YES
    (1,4): h_hat_c5 =    -5.5000 (sign -), h_hat_ov2 =     2.7500 (sign +), chi(ab) = +
          c5 sign matches -chi(ab)? YES, ov2 sign matches chi(ab)? YES
    (2,3): h_hat_c5 =     5.5000 (sign +), h_hat_ov2 =    -2.7500 (sign -), chi(ab) = -
          c5 sign matches -chi(ab)? YES, ov2 sign matches chi(ab)? YES
    (2,5): h_hat_c5 =     5.5000 (sign +), h_hat_ov2 =    -2.7500 (sign -), chi(ab) = -
          c5 sign matches -chi(ab)? YES, ov2 sign matches chi(ab)? YES
    (4,5): h_hat_c5 =    -5.5000 (sign -), h_hat_ov2 =     2.7500 (sign +), chi(ab) = +
          c5 sign matches -chi(ab)? YES, ov2 sign matches chi(ab)? YES

  Eigenvalue explanation:
  Re(z^5) has D^2 coefficient with sign (-1)^1 = -1 (anti-product)
  tr(A^4) ~ sum |z|^4 has D^2 coefficient with sign +1 (product)
  The cancellation c5+2*ov2=const is FORCED by these opposite signs
  combining with the magnitude relationship.

